{
                "name": "ads__gender",
                "description": "This data comes from user provided gender values. We have 3 values in the data as 1, 2 and 3. They represent male, female and (neither 1 or 2) add your gender.                 "data types in tf": "tf.string",
                "model feature type": "categorical"
}

A set of features generated, served, and used by Timelines Quality to add value to authors, but are generally useful for any user. These features are not considered core because Social Graph Service provides similar ones which are more complete, correct (updated in realtime), and has higher throughput capabilities. Note that these features are available in the same dataset as original_author_aggregates features in FS1.0, but in a different table in FS2.0

Reply Count: Number of times the promoted tweet has been replied to



Retweet Count: Number of times the promoted tweet has been retweeted



Total Engagement Count: The sum of the previous 4 counts per promoted tweet ID.
